description: Squats are a compound exercise that works the muscles in your legs, including your quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes.
Push-ups are a bodyweight exercise that primarily targets the muscles in your chest, shoulders, and triceps.
Deadlifts are a compound exercise that targets the muscles in your back, legs, and core.
The bench press is a compound exercise that primarily targets the muscles in your chest, shoulders, and triceps.
Pull-ups are a bodyweight exercise that targets the muscles in your back and biceps.
The plank is an isometric exercise that strengthens the muscles in your core, including your abs, back, and hips.
